The article is about Executive Order 13490, issued by President Barack Obama on January 21, 2009. The order establishes ethics commitments for executive branch personnel. The order requires every appointee in every executive agency appointed on or after January 20, 2009, to sign an ethics pledge. The pledge includes commitments such as not accepting gifts from registered lobbyists, not participating in matters related to former employers or clients, and abiding by post-employment restrictions. The order also establishes definitions for terms used in the pledge and provides provisions for waivers, administration, and enforcement. The order is aimed at promoting ethical behavior and integrity in the executive branch.